videoSnippet.title: One Vlad Retires, Another Rises! | Yangyi Yu vs Artemiev | Gibraltar Masters (2019)
videoSnippet.description:
Follow me on Instagram for extra content https://www.instagram.com/agadmator/

Yangyi Yu vs Vladislav Artemiev 
Gibraltar Masters (2019), Catalan Bay GIB, rd 10, Jan-31 
Caro-Kahn Defense: Advance, Short Variation (B12)

1. e4 c6 2. d4 d5 3. e5 Bf5 4. Nf3 e6 5. Be2 Nd7 6. O-O Bg6 7. c3 Nh6 8. a4 a5 9. Na3 Be7 10. Nc2 O-O 11. Nce1 c5 12. Bxh6 gxh6 13. Bb5 cxd4 14. cxd4 Nb8 15. Qd2 Kg7 16. Nd3 Na6 17. Nf4 Qb6 18. h4 Rfc8 19. Rfc1 Rxc1+ 20. Rxc1 Nb4 21. g3 Na2 22. Rd1 Rc8 23. Nh2 Qc7 24. Bd3 h5 25. g4 Nb4 26. Bxg6 hxg6 27. gxh5 Qc2 28. hxg6 Qf5 29. Qe3 fxg6 30. Qg3 Rf8 31. Ng2 Qc2 32. Ne3 Qe4 33. Neg4 Nc6 34. Qe3 Rf4 35. Nf6 Bxf6 36. exf6+ Kxf6 37. Qxe4 Rxe4 38. Nf3 Ne7 39. Kg2 Nf5 40. Rd3 Nxh4+ 41. Nxh4 Rxh4 42. Kg3 g5 43. Kg2 Re4 44. Kg3 Kf5 45. Kg2 g4 46. Kf1 b6 47. Kg2 Re1 48. b3 Ke4 49. Rd2 Rb1 50. Kg3 Kf5 51. Rd3 Rh1 52. Kg2 Rh3

The 17th Gibraltar Masters is taking place in the Caleta Hotel, Gibraltar from 22-31 January 2019. The 10-round, 250-player open sees stars such as Aronian, MVL, Nakamura and So compete for a £25,000 first prize, while the women's top prize of £15,000 has again attracted many of the world's best female players.

Players receive 100 minutes for 40 moves, followed by 50 minutes for 20 moves, then 15 minutes until the end of the game, with a 30-second increment from move one. A tie for first place will be settled in a speed play-off. The Gibraltar Chess Festival also features four separate amateur tournaments. Official website: www.gibchess.com
